description:
Add endpoint to delete a tick via API.

## Endpoint

```
DELETE /api/projects/:project/ticks/:tickId
```

## Response (204 No Content)

Success - tick deleted.

## Response (404 Not Found)

```json
{
  "error": "Tick not found"
}
```

## Implementation

```typescript
// DELETE /api/projects/:project/ticks/:tickId
if (tickMatch && request.method === "DELETE") {
  const tickId = tickMatch[1];

  if (!this.ticks.has(tickId)) {
    return Response.json({ error: "Tick not found" }, { status: 404 });
  }

  this.ticks.delete(tickId);
  await this.persistState();
  this.broadcast({ type: "tick_deleted", id: tickId });

  const userId = request.headers.get("X-User-Id") || "unknown";
  console.log(`[ProjectRoom:${this.projectId}] Tick ${tickId} deleted via API by ${userId}`);

  return new Response(null, { status: 204 });
}
```

## Warning

Deletion is permanent. Consider:
- Requiring confirmation header: `X-Confirm-Delete: true`
- Or only allowing close (not delete) via API
- Logging deletions for audit

## Files to modify

- `cloud/worker/src/project-room.ts`
